Associated Government Software Clause:

Separation of Software:
This Software, referred to as "SigmaNuPy", is designed to be used in conjunction with MCNP6.1 United States government software, but it is an independent work, not associated with the development, distribution, or licensing of the U.S. government software. The source code and intellectual property rights of the associated U.S. government software remain the property of the U.S. Government. This Software does not provide the source code for the U.S. government software.

Access to Government Software:
To use "SigmaNuPy" in conjunction with the United States government software MCNP6.1, users must separately obtain a license for the U.S. government software. This can be done by visiting https://rsicc.ornl.gov/ and completing the necessary forms to be approved and granted a license. It is the user's responsibility to comply with all terms and conditions set forth in the license agreement for the U.S. government software.

No Liability for Government Software:
The authors of "SigmaNuPy" assume no responsibility and shall not be liable for any claims, damages, or other liabilities arising from the use of the associated U.S. government software. Users of "SigmaNuPy" must understand that any issues, defects, or legal matters pertaining to the U.S. government software are the sole responsibility of the entity providing the U.S. government software, and not of the authors of "SigmaNuPy".
